    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-04-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-04-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="593"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d593">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Thompson</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-04-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 10, 1893</hi>
                        </date>. (Received April 10, 1893.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Thompson announces the return of Mr. Newberry, whose report affords a
                    sufficient basis for the folio wing demands: The issuance of an <hi
                        rend="italic">iradé</hi> in favor of the school, the assurance of adequate
                    protection, the immediate granting of a permit to build, and the payment of 500
                    Turkish pounds, value of the destroyed building, and requests instructions.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
